(11, 'HTML Basic Examples', '', 1, '&lt;p class=&quot;intro&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: #404040; margin-top: 10px;&quot;&gt;Don''t worry if these examples use tags you have not learned.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;intro&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: #404040; margin-top: 10px;&quot;&gt;You will learn them in the next chapters.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;hr style=&quot;color: #d4d4d4; height: 1px; border: 0px; clear: both; font-size: 14px; background-color: #d4d4d4;&quot; /&gt;\r\n&lt;h2 style=&quot;font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;HTML Documents&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: #404040; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;All HTML documents must start with a type declaration:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE html&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: #404040; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The HTML document itself begins with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and ends with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: #404040; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The visible part of the HTML document is between&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;body&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;h2 class=&quot;example&quot; style=&quot;font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: normal; color: #444444; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;example&quot; style=&quot;width: auto; border: 1px solid #ebebeb; margin: 0px; padding: 10px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f1f1f1;&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;example_code notranslate htmlHigh&quot; style=&quot;width: auto; padding: 4px 4px 4px 7px; border-left-width: 4px; border-left-style: solid; bor